    <main id="content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="post-content">
          <h1>Accessible In-Page Navigation</h1>
          <p>This guide provides instructions for creating an in-page navigation component that meets accessibility standards.</p>

          <h2>Interactive Example</h2>
          <div class="usa-in-page-nav-container">
            <aside class="usa-in-page-nav" aria-labelledby="nav-title">
              <h4 id="nav-title">On this page</h4>
              <a href="#section1">Section 1</a>
              <a href="#section2">Section 2</a>
              <a href="#section3">Section 3</a>
            </aside>
            <main id="main-content" class="main-content usa-prose">
              <h2 id="section1">Section 1</h2>
              <p>Content for section 1...</p>

              <h2 id="section2">Section 2</h2>
              <p>Content for section 2...</p>

              <h2 id="section3">Section 3</h2>
              <p>Content for section 3...</p>
            </main>
          </div>

          <h2>Source Code</h2>
          <pre><code>&lt;div class="usa-in-page-nav-container"&gt;
  &lt;aside class="usa-in-page-nav" aria-labelledby="nav-title"&gt;
    &lt;h4 id="nav-title"&gt;On this page&lt;/h4&gt;
    &lt;a href="#section1"&gt;Section 1&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a href="#section2"&gt;Section 2&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a href="#section3"&gt;Section 3&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/aside&gt;
  &lt;main id="main-content" class="main-content usa-prose"&gt;
    &lt;h2 id="section1"&gt;Section 1&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Content for section 1...&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;h2 id="section2"&gt;Section 2&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Content for section 2...&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;h2 id="section3"&gt;Section 3&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Content for section 3...&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/main&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

          <h2>Guidance</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Use in-page navigation for long pages with multiple sections to improve the user experience.</li>
            <li>Ensure that the navigation links reflect the corresponding section headings on the page.</li>
            <li>Place the in-page navigation in a sticky position beside the main content for easy access.</li>
            <li>Ensure the in-page navigation is keyboard-accessible, allowing users to navigate using the `Tab` key.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Focus states are clearly defined for keyboard navigation.</li>
            <li>Link text is descriptive and matches the corresponding section headings.</li>
            <li>Color contrast in links meets WCAG 2.1 AA standards for visibility.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

